place.name: YATTON KEYNELL
place.gazetteerText: YATTON-KEYNELL, a parish in Chippenham district, Wilts; 4 miles WNW of Chippenham r. station. It has a post-office under Chippenham. Acres, 1,749. Real property, £3,488; of which £12 are in quarries. Pop., 554. Houses, 117. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Gloucester and Bristol. Value, £500.* Patron, B. Pinniger, Esq. The church was lately restored. There are a Baptist chapel and a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
